President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These include L. Wayne Brasure as Director for Domestic Nuclear Detection at the Department of Homeland Security, Peter Van Dyck Emerson as a member of the President's Commission on White House Fellowships, Robert D. Alverson as the United States Commissioner for the International Pacific Halibut Commission, Victor R. McCrary and Emilio F. Moran as members of the National Science Board at the National Science Foundation, Philip Anderson as the United States Commissioner for the Pacific Salmon Commission, Susan Levine, Elliot J. Schrage, Irvin Shapell, Howard Unger, and Clemantine Wamariya as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. President Obama expressed his gratitude to these individuals for their willingness to serve the American people.